<br>
Part 1:<br>
<br>
On a multi-day zone Rotation, a guild may leave the zone and not be done with their &quot;turn&quot;. It's their &quot;turn&quot; for the amount of days said zone is allowed.<br>
<br>
Part 2:<br>
<br>
If you choose to be on a multi-day rotation, you are given the courtesy that no other guild/alliance will go in when you log for the night. The return from you (said guild/alliance) is that you give up any other Rotation Mob that you are up for, UNTIL you declare your 'turn' in the multiday zone over. <br>
<br>
Notice Part 2... once you start your &quot;turn&quot; on a multi-day Rotation, you give up all your other Rotation Mobs.  That is to say.. you cannot leave VT on day 2 of your 3 day rotation to kill KT and then go back in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nilasu>Nilasu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(5/16/03 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> OK, I just need a quick claraifcation:<br>
<br>
Nyca said<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>once you start your &quot;turn&quot; on a multi-day Rotation, you give up all your other Rotation Mobs. That is to say.. you cannot leave VT on day 2 of your 3 day rotation to kill KT and then go back in<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Milambus said<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Once you begin your turn on a rotation, you should follow it through, and not use the fact that it is on rotation to allow you to get more mobs<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So lets say GuildA has 3 rotations due on Monday (lets include VT and NToV in the same day for arguments), 1 rotation due on Tuesday, and 1 due on Wednesday.<br>
<br>
Scenario 1:<br>
If GuildA start the day of by heading to NToV, they basically forfeit all their other rotations for that day, is that correct? So basically any guild who starts a multi-day rotation forfeits all their other rotations and auto-passes them to the next guild in rotation.<br>
<br>
Scenario 2:<br>
How does this work if you have multi-day rots due the same day? For example if GuildA has over 120 people, and they are due for NToV and VT. Lets say GuildA splits their guild into 2 raid party. One can start NToV and the other can do VT. Is this still within the RTA rules?<br>
<br>
Scenario 3:<br>
What happens if you are in the middle of a multi-day raid and your other rot pops up? Example: You start VT on Monday. You basically have to pass on all your Rots on Tuesday and Wednesday, since VT is a 3 day raid. If you have to pass per rule, any guild caught killing their rot mobs during VT is basically in violation of RTA. Correct? <br>
<br>
Clarification on this would be nice. Thanks. I do have to say that it does limit you to what rotation you really want to be on, and you have to think about the order in which you do your rot mobs. <p>Elder Nilasu Whiteheart<br>
